true if the volume format treats upper and lower case characters in file and directory names as different. Otherwise an upper case character is equivalent to a lower case character, and you can’t have two names that differ solely in the case of the characters.

true if the volume supports reliable storage of times for the root directory.

inlineContent.text: URLs to file system resources support the properties defined below. Note that not all property values will exist for all file system URLs. For example, if a file is located on a volume that does not support creation dates, it is valid to request the creation date property, but the returned value will be
, and no error will be generated.
Only the fields requested by the keys you pass into the
function to receive this value will be populated. The others will return
regardless of the underlying property on the file system.
As a convenience, volume resource values can be requested from any file system URL. The value returned will reflect the property value for the volume on which the resource is located.
